    "recap_headline": "James Madison University | Official Athletics Site",
    "recap_text": "CONWAY, S.C. \u2013\nJames Madison got out to a 4-0 lead, but a six-run third inning led No. 16 Coastal Carolina to take down the Dukes, 16-6, in seven innings on Sunday afternoon at Spring Brooks Stadium in Sun Belt Conference baseball.\nThe Dukes fell to 11-11 (3-3 Sun Belt), while the Chanticleers improved to 16-7 (6-0 Sun Belt).\nLeading JMU at the plate was redshirt sophomore\nClay Thompson\n, going 2-for-4 with a run scored\nHow It Happened\nSecond Inning\nBack-to-back singles, each with a runner in scoring position, from senior\nWyatt Campbell\nand sophomore\nJack Anderson\nput JMU ahead 2-0.\nThird Inning\nThe Dukes loaded the bases to bring up senior\nJack Cannizzaro\n, who lined a double into the left field corner to bring two runs in and make it 4-0 in favor of JMU.\nCoastal responded by bringing 11 batters to the plate, pushing seven runs across to take a 7-4 lead.\nFourth Inning\nSophomore\nReece Moody\nbrought the Dukes within a run of the Chants, hitting a two-run double after juniors\nKyle Langley\nand\nIke Schmidly\neach hit base hits of their own to begin the inning.\nA two-run homer from Rex Watson pushed the lead back to three for the Chants, at 9-6.\nFifth Inning\nCCU took a 14-6 lead after batting around and scratching across five runs.\nSixth Inning\nThe Chants took a 10-run lead with a pair of runs.\nGame Notes\nAll nine batters in the starting lineup recorded a hit for the Dukes.\nJMU batted .571 (8-for-14) with runners on and .545 (6-for-11) with runners in scoring position.\nUp Next\nThe Dukes return home to host Radford on Tuesday, March 24 with a 4 p.m. first pitch, before going back on the road to face Arkansas State over the weekend.",
